{"id":14881728,"mediaExerciseId":"c21b1660-69e4-42f5-aaa4-12edb36c4bfb","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"20","chapterTitle":"Credit and Inventory Management","groupId":612459,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":701,"solutions":[{"id":6047787,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to determine  Arizona Bay Corporation’s balance sheet amount in accounts receivable. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":" Assume $365$ days per year. First, we will find the receivable turnover as follows \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Receivable turnover}&=\\frac{\\text{Number of days in the year}}{\\text{Average collection period}}\\\\\n&=\\frac{365\\hspace{2mm}\\text{days}}{30+5}\\\\\n&=\\frac{365\\hspace{2mm}\\text{days}}{35\\hspace{2mm}\\text{days}}\\\\\n&=10.428571\\\\\n&\\approx10 \n\\end{align*}$$\n**Hence, accounts receivable turnover is approximately 10 days.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":" The company’s balance sheet amount in accounts receivable is\n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Average accounts receivable}&=\\frac{\\text{Annual credit sales}}{\\text{Receivable turnover}}\\\\\n&=\\frac{8,350,000}{10.428571}\\\\\n&=\\$800,684.96\n\\end{align*}$$\n**Hence, the average accounts receivable is $800,684.96**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"2c5fe860-e57d-4d90-bf8c-d612b40eba20","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","ima